HEADWORD: Tough-pitch
<hw>Tough"-pitch`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Metal.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The exact state or quality of texture and consistency
of well reduced and refined copper.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Copper so
reduced; -- called also <altname>tough-cake</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Touite</ent>⟦br⟧
